The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Bata profit rises 18%
                                                                                                               Bata profit rises 18%
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, March 29: Bata India has reported an 18.15 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 47.4 crore for the year ended December 2007 compared with Rs 40.1 crore in the previous year.        
	Total income of the company during the period stood at Rs 880.5 crore against Rs 797.3 crore in the same period last year year. Marcelo Villagran, managing director of Bata India, said the company delivered the best results ever with a profit before tax of Rs 55.15 crore in its 75th year.        
	The company has now become profitable on a sustained basis. We will continue to grow our sales, improve our margins and monitor the expenses, he said, adding that the company was on an aggressive growth path. Bata has set an ambitious target of opening 70 stores every year for the next few years.        
	The company has introduced exclusive Hush Puppies stores for the first time in India. The board also declared a dividend of 20 per cent, inclusive of the 5 per cent additional dividend offered earlier.                                                                                                                                       
